				<td colspan="2"><span>Couple of things about this, is I'm not sure if it always did this sort of stuff, the HoTT window definatley helps to show what's happening, and did I just not notice before?
<br />
Then again, OoW aggro does appear different, party members have commented on this a few times.  Noticed alot of wierd aggro behavior, things like you've mentioned, even the afk party member being pounced on suddenly, even though we know they never did anything.  Some sort of wierd rampage, without the rampage announcement.  Hard to describe, but aggro can definately move around.  One other thing different I've seen happen, is a mezd mob, breaking mez, instead of charging towards the chanter/me/or healer, going for the rogue, no idea how aggro transferred onto the rogue, but like I said, aggro in OoW just seems different, and I'm not sure exactly what it's doing.  If nothing else, it appears to be keeping everyone on their toes a bit more than usual.
<br />

<br />
Jyve afk</span></td>
