				<td colspan="2"><span>This a very old feature. Well, it was like that when i started to play a bard which was in LDoN times.
<br />

<br />
The Way it work is pretty simple. Whatever happen, the first person who get on aggro list receive the detrimental spell. In another word, who ever pull it receive dispel/snare etc. 
<br />

<br />
Imho, its very dumb AI considering the game mechanic. I dont know about you all but the last thing I care about is what buff are on me. I got dispelled so often that it just dont worth it to get rebuffed, more efficient to play buffless. Side tracked here, the main advantage is that it doesnt debuff your tank, thus saving buffers lots of mana.
<br />

<br />
Honestly, when you pull a caster and you fade, you better aggro it very quick before the tank do it or you'll have a rebuff session down time.</span></td>
