				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Mob hating me enough to cast a spell but not hit me??<a name="67085"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 15 04 2:34 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Here's what I think happens:
<br />

<br />
When meleeing, one of the factors in determining who the MOB attacks is &quot;distance to target&quot;.  The tank is usually closest, so s/he gets a little extra aggro.  When the MOB casts spells, though, perhaps the distance to target isn't calculated, so now the Bard who is 50 feet away is considered equally with the tank who is 1 foot away.
<br />

<br />
Just a theory.  I can confirm that this has always happened, also.</span></td>
